      "text": "PMC PIPELINE  (ingestion/pmc/)  —  PubMed Central Open Access",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "PMC PIPELINE  (ingestion/pmc/)  —  PubMed Central Open Access",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "index": "b2y",
      "autoResize": true
    },
    {
      "id": "in_pmc_txt",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1328,
      "y": 4484,
      "width": 1284,
      "height": 378,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#334155",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 20458,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 1454384597,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777442117487,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "pmc_oa_ingest.py  (113 KB — main ingestion script)\n\nPipeline stages\n  1. Fetch PubMed Central open-access articles via OAI-PMH protocol\n  2. Parse article XML → extract abstract, body sections, metadata\n  3. Semantic chunking (section-aware: abstract / methods / results / discussion)\n  4. Embed via OpenAI text-embedding-3-large  (1536-dim)\n  5. Upsert → Qdrant qwiva_docs  +  guideline_chunks (PubMed Supabase table)\n\nMetadata extracted per chunk\n  pmid, pmcid, title, journal, publication_date\n  mesh_terms, authors, doc_type='pubmed'\n  evidence_tier  (RCT / systematic review / case series / expert opinion)\n\nCorpus focus\n  HIV/ARV, malaria, TB, maternal + neonatal health\n  paediatrics, nutrition — East Africa / Sub-Saharan focus\n\nConfig\n  railway.json  — Railway cloud deployment\n  requirements.txt  — requests, qdrant-client, openai, pydantic",
      "fontSize": 9,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "pmc_oa_ingest.py  (113 KB — main ingestion script)\n\nPipeline stages\n  1. Fetch PubMed Central open-access articles via OAI-PMH protocol\n  2. Parse article XML → extract abstract, body sections, metadata\n  3. Semantic chunking (section-aware: abstract / methods / results / discussion)\n  4. Embed via OpenAI text-embedding-3-large  (1536-dim)\n  5. Upsert → Qdrant qwiva_docs  +  guideline_chunks (PubMed Supabase table)\n\nMetadata extracted per chunk\n  pmid, pmcid, title, journal, publication_date\n  mesh_terms, authors, doc_type='pubmed'\n  evidence_tier  (RCT / systematic review / case series / expert opinion)\n\nCorpus focus\n  HIV/ARV, malaria, TB, maternal + neonatal health\n  paediatrics, nutrition — East Africa / Sub-Saharan focus\n\nConfig\n  railway.json  — Railway cloud deployment\n  requirements.txt  — requests, qdrant-client, openai, pydantic",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "index": "b2z",
      "autoResize": true
    },
